== English ==
=== History ===
[[Shakespeare]]; from ''[[Hamlet]]'' (III.iv.207)
:''For tis the sport to haue the [[enginer]] / Hoist with his owne '''petar'''''

=== Idiom ===
'''(to) [[hoist]] by one's own [[petard]]'''
# (literally) to be 'blown up by one's own bomb'
# (figuratively) to have a situation of one's own doing lead to one's [[downfall]]
#: ''he has no one to blame but himself; he was '''hoisted by his own petard'''''
